apx is a CLI tool for managing, publishing, and consuming API schemas across organizations.

Usage:
  apx [command]

Available Commands:
  add         Add a dependency to apx.yaml and apx.lock
  breaking    Check for breaking changes in schema files
  catalog     Catalog operations
  completion  Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  config      Configuration operations
  fetch       Download and cache toolchain dependencies for offline use
  gen         Generate code
  help        Help about any command
  init        Initialize a new schema module or canonical repository
  lint        Validate schema files for syntax and style issues
  policy      Policy operations
  publish     Publish a module to canonical repository
  search      Search for APIs in the catalog
  semver      Semantic version operations
  sync        Synchronize go.work overlays with canonical imports
  unlink      Remove overlay and switch to published module

Flags:
      --config string   config file path (default "apx.yaml")
  -h, --help            help for apx
      --json            output in JSON format
      --no-color        disable colored output
  -q, --quiet           suppress output
      --verbose         verbose output
  -v, --version         version for apx

Use "apx [command] --help" for more information about a command.
